An example of a sequential search algorithm in Python would be as follows:|

def sequential_search(list, value):
	for i in range(len(list)):
		if list[i] == value:
			return i
	return -1

|In this algorithm, the list of elements is traversed one by one and each element is compared to the searched value. If the value is found, the position at which it is found in the list is returned. If it is not found, -1 is returned.
